com.dougnoel.sentinel.elements

Class ElementFunctions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.dougnoel.sentinel.elements.ElementFunctions

  • public abstract class ElementFunctions
extends Object
    Retrieves as an element as a PageElement or as one of the following types: - Button, Checkbox, Div, Dropdown, GoogleMap, Link, Radio, Select, Span, Table, Textbox To return as the desired type, we call getElement which returns a PageElement, and the element is then typecast as the desired element.

      • getElement

        public static PageElement getElement(String elementName)
                              throws NoSuchElementException,
                                     PageNotFoundException
        Returns a PageElement object for a given elementName string from current page. Gets current page reference, replaces page name space characters qith '_'
        Parameters:
        elementName - String name of requested element
        Returns:
        PageElement the requested element
        Throws:
        PageNotFoundException - if no page object found or defined.
        NoSuchElementException - if element is not found or defined.
